		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=402"><span id=Scholar>Sage</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>18 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.60]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'm going to have to disagree on the usefulness of DOTs in groups, though it entirely depends on what you're hunting and your group's makeup.&nbsp;&nbsp;The real question is how long it takes to kill the mob (which was alluded to in the post).  If you're pushing the edge with your group, you'll probably need to use DOTs when fighting one big nasty rather than groups of smaller ones.<br><br>What you said is true for relatively quick kills, but if you're hunting something that takes your group a long time to kill (say, hill giants at level 30 in a group of four), the mob will sometimes outlive the DOTs.  Of course, it's seldom worth recasting a DOT unless the mob is over half health.  If that's the case, you've probably got bigger problems... ;-)<br><br>Also, the flame-series DOT lowers the mob's AC for your tank, so it's worth casting even on high blues if they're lasting very long before dying, and especially if you've got more than one person whacking away.<br><br>Depending on your group and what you're fighting, the ensnare, pull and let get mad at your tank, DOT, DOT, med approach may be more effective.  For short-lived mobs, just a few DD's works better.<br><br>The higher level you and the mobs get, the less time you'll find you survive if the mob gets really mad at you instead of the tank.  [If you suddenly decide to switch to kiting in a misplaced effort to survive, you're really going to tick off the tank(s) trying to taunt the mob off you and the cleric whose heal was almost finished casting when you ran out of range.]  So, saving a couple DD's for near the end of battle isn't a bad idea.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></tabl